{{!
    @template local_dimensions/central/showhidden_toggle

    Standalone "show hidden rows" pill toggle, shared by the three hub tabs (Structures,
    Competencies and Learning plans) so the control looks identical everywhere. The calling
    tab renders it only when hidden content actually exists (the context object is null
    otherwise), and each tab keeps its own data-action so its own JS drives the behaviour.

    The hidden checkbox still drives :checked / :focus-visible on the following track via the
    shared local-dimensions-plans-switch-* mechanics; the wrapper lays the toggle out first
    with the label to its right (see local-dimensions-central-showhidden in styles.css).

    Context variables required:
    * id (string) - the checkbox id
    * label (string) - the (already localised) visible label
    * action (string) - the data-action value the tab's JS listens for
    * checked (bool) - whether the toggle starts on

    Example context (json):
    {
        "id": "local-dimensions-frameworks-showhidden",
        "label": "Show hidden structures",
        "action": "toggle-hidden",
        "checked": false
    }
}}
<label class="local-dimensions-central-showhidden">
    <input type="checkbox" class="local-dimensions-plans-switch-input local-dimensions-central-showhidden-input"
           id="{{id}}" data-action="{{action}}"{{#checked}} checked{{/checked}}>
    <span class="local-dimensions-plans-switch-track" aria-hidden="true"><span class="local-dimensions-plans-switch-knob"></span></span>
    <span class="local-dimensions-central-showhidden-text">{{label}}</span>
</label>
